"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">circles us back</a> to the Betam=
ax opinion, which stands for the precedent that
manufacturers of technologies capable of non-infringing uses are not liable=
 for contributory copyright infringement. The defendants are shooting for t=
hat same principle to be applied here. =E2=80=9CThe doctrine absolves =E2=
=80=A6 mere understanding that the product will be misused,=E2=80=9D argued=
 Gass.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Susman Godfrey partner <strong>Ian Crosby</stron=
g> countered that, back in the =E2=80=9980s, Sony didn=E2=80=99t <em>preloa=
d</em> its VCRs with
millions of movies and TV shows, nor did Sony oversee how buyers were opera=
ting it. =E2=80=9CWhereas here, they are selling a service built on copyrig=
hted works and continuing to operate it,=E2=80=9D he said, arguing that bec=
ause of the company=E2=80=99s continued oversight, one can infer its knowle=
dge that some users might be doing things like using ChatGPT to evade paywa=
lls. In written briefing, the <em>Times</em> lawyers also added, =E2=80=9CI=
f VCRs had been built with movies to make movies that compete with movies, =
=E2=80=A6 [the]
<em>Sony</em> [Supreme Court ruling] would have gone the other way.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Anyone expecting a quick decision from the ju=
dge came away disappointed. Still, there were subtle signs that Stein wasn=
=E2=80=99t prepared to let the defendants off the hook. Much of what was di=
scussed seemed to turn on factual issues, which the judge noted at several =
points. And that=E2=80=99s not something that will be resolved at the
motion-to-dismiss phase. As for the all-important topic of fair use, that=
=E2=80=99s a debate everyone expects will have to be resolved at trial.=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;">I=E2=80=99m sure once this proceeding gets there, OpenAI and Microsof=
t will have further opportunities to tell a jury the old lesson about the i=
ndustry=E2=80=99s VCR problem, with the <em>Times</em> and its Susman Godfr=
ey team responding with tales of greedy tech companies encroaching on entir=
e
industries. Whether this narrative will echo the catastrophic predictions o=
f yesteryear remains to be seen, but its impact could be as profound as the=
 landmark cases of the past.=C2=A0</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
